Jon:

I have been working on a remapping of Jerome, (the key to character
correspondence, not the technical side of it) which I feel will work
much better than what we have been using.  I will get a post to you
setting it out as soon as I can.

Paige



Jon Zuck wrote:

&gt;  You&#39;re absolutely right, Rick. Jerome went through quite a bit of
&gt; evolution,
&gt; and at first I was quite hesitant to go the distance of the
&gt; half-letters,
&gt; and all. However, Paige convinced me, rightly, that there should be a
&gt; font
&gt; that could emulate the full Senior Quickscript capabilities,
&gt; particularly
&gt; when presenting its virtues to the Shavian community, which already
&gt; had a
&gt; non-cursive Shavian font.
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;ve uploaded to this group a copy of the poster of the Lord&#39;s Prayer
&gt; which
&gt; I uploaded a few hours after my initial upload of Jerome. You can see
&gt; the
&gt; difference: Junior Quickscriptish, very easy-to-read, etc.
&gt;
&gt; The thing is that there are really three Shavian alphabets: Shavian,
&gt; Junior,and Senior.  I think most people who are not adverse to cursive
&gt;
&gt; writing :-) will eventually find Senior the more preferable one for
&gt; personal
&gt; handwriting, which is the most practical use for a semi-private
&gt; alphabet
&gt; that only a handful of people can read. But for the computer, in
&gt; English, we
&gt; usually only use cursive fonts for art, titles, special emphasis, and
&gt; the
&gt; feeling of a &quot;personal touch.&quot;  On the other hand, many languages of
&gt; world
&gt; use connected, cursive letters: Hindi, Bengali, Arabic, Aramaic. I
&gt; felt
&gt; after much correspondence with Paige that Read was clearly touting the
&gt; more
&gt; cursive capabilities of Senior QA, which should connect.
&gt;
&gt; But thanks for giving us again a Junior font.  It is more legible,
&gt; more
&gt; suitable for screen.
&gt;
&gt; As long as all there&#39;s interest in all three alphabets, fonts for all
&gt; three
&gt; should be avail. My only concern is the minor changes to the mapping.
&gt; We
&gt; don&#39;t need three mappings. I think a Read-based mapping is desireable,
&gt; but
&gt; on the other hand so is backward compatibility to Shavian--not so much
&gt; to
&gt; lure them over, but to use their transliteration programs, which is
&gt; why I
&gt; kept it in Jerome. (Bad as their mapping is, the fact that they
&gt; created a
&gt; standard and built upon it is great.)
&gt;
&gt; BTW, I realized that my key to the Second Shaw Alphabet, originally
&gt; posted
&gt; to the Shavian group wasn&#39;t on the files in this group and the
&gt; Shavian&#39;s
&gt; copy was corrupted.  I fixed it and posted it to both.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Shalom v&#39;Tovah,
&gt;
&gt; Jon
&gt; http://surf.to/frimmin
&gt;
&gt; It is more necessary to love much than to think much;
&gt; always do that which impels you most to love.
